From 3b7124b3738ba3f5eeed14c40ab4d1fd8a11fa13 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chronium Build <chronium@interlink.local>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 16:55:09 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 04/14] chronium: sync seed propagation, getImageData noise,
 WebGL unmasked_* spoof

Bundles three fingerprint-surface improvements that share infra
changes (chrome_switches, content_browser_client, content_renderer_
client). Each is independently testable and verified.

A. Synchronous seed propagation (kills the canvas race)
   Previously the seed traveled browser->renderer via async Mojo,
   so a canvas readback from a top-level inline <script> could run
   before the seed arrived and miss the noise. Fix: the browser now
   appends --fingerprint-seed-hex=<64 hex chars> to every child
   process command line via AppendExtraCommandLineSwitches, and the
   renderer parses it in RenderThreadStarted *before* any document
   is created. Result: canvas (and every later fingerprint vector)
   has the seed available from the very first byte of HTML parsing.
   The Mojo channel from patch 0002 is kept as a no-op fallback;
   FingerprintState::Set is idempotent.

B. CanvasRenderingContext2D::getImageData noise
   Patch 0003 only noised toDataURL/toBlob. getImageData is the other
   common readback path. After BaseRenderingContext2D's
   getImageDataInternal calls readPixels into the returned ImageData
   pixmap, we run the same LSB-flip loop, keyed by the same 'canvas'
   channel and canvas-space (sx+x, sy+y) coordinates so a pixel
   noised one way through toDataURL is noised the same way through
   getImageData (cross-API consistency within profile).

C. WebGL UNMASKED_VENDOR_WEBGL / UNMASKED_RENDERER_WEBGL spoof
   Extends FingerprintState with SetWebGLStrings/WebGLUnmasked* and
   FingerprintProfile with WebGLUnmaskedVendor/Renderer accessors
   reading from the JSON 'webgl' dict. Browser propagates the two
   strings via --fingerprint-webgl-vendor / --fingerprint-webgl-
   renderer switches. WebGLRenderingContextBase::getParameter's
   case branches for kUnmaskedRendererWebgl (37446) and
   kUnmaskedVendorWebgl (37445) now return the spoofed strings
   when set; falls through to the real driver values otherwise.

Verified A+B+C on a single test page:
- profile A: toDataURL hash -356449597, getImageData sum 93240642,
  UNMASKED_VENDOR NVIDIA Corporation, UNMASKED_RENDERER NVIDIA
  GeForce RTX 3060/PCIe/SSE2
- profile B: toDataURL hash 1834648629, getImageData sum -74073189,
  UNMASKED_VENDOR Intel Inc., UNMASKED_RENDERER Intel(R) UHD
  Graphics 630
All hashes deterministic across multiple reads within a profile.

